{"lemma":"قَلْسَيْ","slug":"قَلْسَيْ","root":"ق.ل.س","root_slug":"ق-ل-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ل-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36138","","n36141","n36142"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put the قَلَنْسُوَة (qalansuwa) on"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mock, to deride"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to receive with songs or dance performances","tags":["obsolete","rare"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bow before","tags":["obsolete","rare"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to belch, to regurgitate, to vomit","tags":["obsolete","rare"],"examples":[{"text":"مَنْ أَصَابَهُ قَيْءٌ أَوْ رُعَافٌ, أَوْ قَلَسٌ, أَوْ مَذْيٌ فَلْيَنْصَرِفْ فَلْيَتَوَضَّأْ, ثُمَّ لِيَبْنِ عَلَى صَلَاتِهِ, وَهُوَ فِي ذَلِكَ لَا يَتَكَلَّمُ","english":"Whoever vomits, bleeds through the nose, or released seminal discharge should go, perform ablution and then go over to his prayer, and he may not speak in the process."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of قَلَسَ (qalasa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rope, cable","tags":["obsolete","rare"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb of قَلَنْسُوَة (qalansuwa).\n\nApparently a twentieth-century borrowing (?) from Hebrew קִלֵּס (qilles, “to mock”) = Ugaritic 𐎖𐎍𐎕 (qlṣ, “to scorn”). Semantical doublet of سَلَقَ (salaqa) in the meaning which got borrowed from Ge'ez ተሳለቀ (täsaläḳä, “to scoff at”) (the Ethiopic cognate to the Northwest Semitic by metathesis).\n\nBorrowed from Classical Syriac ܩܰܠܶܣ (qalles, “to praise”), in Jewish Aramaic קַלֵּס, according to Rabin ultimately a bifurcated cultic word that is reflected in the opposite sense as Ugaritic 𐎖𐎍𐎕 (qlṣ, “to scorn”), Hebrew קִלֵּס (qilles, “to mock”) and Ge'ez ተሳለቀ (täsaläḳä, “to scoff at”) and is from Hittite [Term?] (/⁠kalleš-⁠/, “to call, to invite”) from cultic contexts.\n\nApparently onomatopoeic.\n\nFrom Ancient Greek κάλως (kálōs, “rope, cable”). Aramaic but found as Classical Syriac ܩܠܣܐ at Bar Bahlul."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36138","headword_ar":"قَلَسَ","root":"qls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalosN","text_ar":"قَلْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He belched up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * A, * Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his throat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his belly, to his mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as much as filled his mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acid and undigested"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drink, whether he cast it forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returned it to his belly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"when it overcomes [or is repeated (accord. to an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalosN","text_ar":"قَلْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalasN","text_ar":"قَلَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below,)] it [the action] is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaYo'N","text_ar":"قَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he vomited"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaA='a","text_ar":"قَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as much as filled his mouth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, vomited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cast forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qa*afa","text_ar":"قَذَفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) The act termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalosN","text_ar":"قَلْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an impurity which necessitates the performance of the ablution termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuDuwo'","text_ar":"وُضُوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, Mgh:) so in a trad. (A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalasato nafosuhu","text_ar":"قَلَسَتْ نَفْسُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His soul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stomach, heaved;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became agitated by a tendency to vomit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqisato","text_ar":"لَقِسَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalasati","text_ar":"قَلَسَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aEonapu biAld~ami","text_ar":"الطَّعْنَةُ بِالدَّمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wound made with a spear or the like belched forth blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalasati","text_ar":"قَلَسَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aHaAbapu biAln~adaY","text_ar":"السَّحَابَةُ بِالنَّدَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cloud cast forth moisture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fine rain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"not vehement rain. (A, * TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalasati AlkaA^osu","text_ar":"قَلَسَتِ الكَاْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, *) aor. and inf. n. as above, (K,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cup of wine cast forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overflowed with"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the beverage, in consequence of its being very full."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K. *) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalasa AlbaHoru","text_ar":"قَلَسَ البَحْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as above, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great river, cast forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overflowed with"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water, in consequence of its being very full."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","Msb","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n36141","headword_ar":"قَلْسٌ","root":"qls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K, and so in a copy of the S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalasN","text_ar":"قَلَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh, Msb, TA, and so in a copy of the S,) the former being the inf. n., (Mgh, Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalasaAnN","text_ar":"قَلَسَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [but this last is more like an inf. n.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What comes forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kh [accord. to the S], or Lth, AZ [accord. to the TA], S, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the throat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kh or Lth, S, A, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the belly, to the mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as much as fills the mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kh or Lth, S, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undigested"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drink,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, Msb,) peculiarly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with acidity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that acid humour itself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Meyd, as cited by Golius,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether the person cast it forth or return it to his belly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, Msb:) when it is repeated, (Kh, S, A, K,) or overcomes, (Lth, TA,) it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaYo'N","text_ar":"قَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Kh or Lth, S, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what comes forth, of vomit, being as much as fills the mouth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqolaAsN","text_ar":"اَقْلَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","TA","AZ","Kh","S","A","K","Lth"]},{"entry_id":"n36142","headword_ar":"قَلَسٌ","root":"qls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalosN","text_ar":"قَلْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}